U.S. Denounced for Aggravating Tensions 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 13 (KCNA) -- Unless the U.S. gives up its double-dealing attitude toward the six-party talks and hostile policy toward the DPRK, the resumption of the talks and the settlement of the nuclear issue cannot be expected.
 Rodong Sinmun Monday says this in a signed commentary.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. hostile policy toward the DPRK is the main obstacle to the resumption of the six-party talks and the settlement of the nuclear issue. The U.S., persistently evading its obligatory implementation, has laid artificial difficulties in the process of the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Whenever a sign of progress was seen at the six-party talks, the U.S. put obstacles to their progress under the pretexts of non-existent "human rights, counterfeit notes and drug smuggling issues". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Even after the 3rd round of the six-party talks in June 2004 agreed on the principle of "words for words" and "action for action" and the principle of "compensation for freeze", a measure of the first phase for the settlement of the nuclear issue, and reached the joint common cognition that the U.S. should change its hostile policy toward the DPRK, thus laying a foundation for the progress of the talks, the U.S. betrayed the principles. Less than a month after the end of the talks, the U.S. totally negated the principle of "compensation for freeze" and, at the same time, rigged up a "north Korean human rights act" to halt the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Just before the 2nd stage of the 4th round of the six-party talks, the U.S. made public a "report" to designate the DPRK as a "violator of the international arms control conventions". It also alleged that the DPRK has pursued the "uranium enrichment program" in secret, "violating" the Joint Declaration on the Denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and the DPRK-U.S. Agreed Framework. When last year witnessed the Sept. 19 joint statement and positive moves for the settlement of the nuclear issue, the U.S. again fabricated "counterfeit notes" and "illegal traffic" to disturb the implementation of the joint statement, thus blocking the resumption of the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the logic of the U.S. hard-line conservative forces and the U.S. stance toward the six-party talks to allege that "dialogue" is no more than a "gesture" to captivate its opponent and the U.S. will for action is "strength". With nothing can the U.S. evade its responsibility for blocking the progress of the six-party talks.

Formation of Umbrella Body of United Front Called for in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 13 (KCNA) -- The 6th meeting of the Reunification Solidarity for Implementing the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and Achieving Peace on the Korean Peninsula held in Seoul on March 8 reportedly discussed as its special agenda item the issue of creating an umbrella body for united front. 
 The Reunification Solidarity decided to formally organize a planning team for creating an umbrella body for united front and wind up the discussion of the above-said issue through consultations with the progressive camp including "the National People's Solidarity" as early as possible within this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It made it clear that the political goal of the umbrella body is to achieve national independence and democracy, regarding the people as a driving force, implement the June 15 joint declaration, realize peaceful reunification and guarantee them the right to their existence and social equality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also declared that it would use the meeting as an occasion of putting spurs to the creation of the umbrella body for the united front, a united political organization for establishing an independent democratic government. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution adopted at the meeting called for achieving strong solidarity of people from all walks of life including workers, farmers, youth and students, women and the poor and the great unity of the nation by the concerted efforts of the forces for independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resolution stressed the need to strengthen the June 15 joint national committee to pave a wide avenue for the progress of great national unity and the implementation of the joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting was followed by a function for commemorating the 5th anniversary of the Reunification Solidarity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was addressed by Han Sang Ryol, permanent representative chairman of the Reunification Solidarity, Jong Kwang Hun, permanent representative of "the National People's Solidarity," Mun Kyong Sik, chairman of "the National Federation of Peasants Associations", Jo Jun Ho, chairman of the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions, Jang Song Hoe, chairman of the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils, and Mun Song Hyon, representative of the Democratic Workers' Party, and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers declared that the way to be followed by the progressive camp in the days ahead is to create an umbrella body for the united front, adding they would take the lead in the actions to attain the goal.

U.S.-led Reckless Joint Military Exercises Blasted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 13 (KCNA) -- The "Team Spirit" joint military exercises were a most dangerous DPRK-targeted test nuclear war in their nature, contents and scale, observes Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article carried 30 years since the U.S. imperialists launched the exercises together with the bellicose forces of south Korea. 
 The south Korean authorities' plan to continue staging large-scale joint military exercises against the DPRK along with the U.S. is a criminal move against the nation, peace and reunification as it will chill the ardent desire of the fellow countrymen for reunification, escalate tension on the Korean Peninsula and do harm to the cause of independent reunification, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Joint military exercises with foreign forces are quite contrary to the spirit of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Staging the joint military exercises with foreign forces explicitly means close "cooperation" with aggressive foreign forces in the political aspect.
 The above-said plan of the south Korean authorities is an outright breach of the joint declaration which calls for refraining from any "cooperation" with foreign forces in war and achieving cooperation for peace in the spirit of "By our nation itself".
 Joint war exercises with outside forces are the factor of exacerbating the tensions on the Korean Peninsula and bedeviling the inter-Korean relations.
 Intolerable are the joint military maneuvers intended to block the just cause of the Korean nation for peace and independent reunification of the country with provocative war gambles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the south Korean authorities truly stand for the development of the inter-Korean relations and peace and reunification on the Korean Peninsula, they should immediately cancel the projected joint military exercises harmful to them.

February Holiday Celebrated Worldwide
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 13 (KCNA) -- Multifarious functions were held in over 70 countries this year to most auspiciously celebrate February 16, the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il, as a holiday common to humankind.
 Preparations to significantly mark this day were pushed forward in all parts of the world from the end of the last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Ugandan National Preparatory Committee for Celebrating February 16 was inaugurated in Kampala in December, 2005, and nearly 50 preparatory committees for celebrating February 16 were organized in many countries and by international organizations this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preparatory committee was organized by officials of the government and political parties in Cambodia under the instructions of the king and preparatory committees with famous political and public figures as chairpersons were formed in Nepal, Bangladesh, Romania, Congo, Tanzania and other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Association for Friendship with the Korean People which has branches in more than 90 countries opened the Internet special homepage and the February 16 International Committee consisting of representatives of East European and Central Asian countries was inaugurated and thus preparations for celebrating the February holiday were conducted on a larger scale. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Foreign media spared no time and space for introduction and information to excite February holiday atmosphere. 
 The Chinese Hong Kong newspaper Ching Pao, the Russian newspaper Patriot, the German newspaper Die Rote Fahne, the Ugandan newspaper Sun Rise, the Brazilian newspaper Hora do Povo, the Indian magazine Social Look, the Italian magazine La Voce, the Guinean Agency of Press, the Lao National TV, Ecuadorian TV Tele Andina 23 and other media carried the portraits and images of Kim Jong Il and widely introduced his brief biography, famous works and personality as a great man who has led not only the Korean revolution but also the cause of global independence to victory with his unique Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Honorary titles, floral baskets and gifts were presented to him in various countries on the occasion of his birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was presented with the honorary title of "Protector and Charitarian of World Art for 2005" and a gift by the Russian International Charity Fund "Protectors of the Art for the Century" at a grand ceremony held at the Kremlin State Palace in Moscow on February 16. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was also awarded the title of honorary citizen of Darhan Ol Province in Mongolia. The titles of honorary citizens of Yantzaza City, Zamora Chinchipe Province, in Ecuador were conferred on the three generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And the Cambodian king, the Equatorial Guinean president, the Guinean president, the Workers' Party of Bangladesh, the Brazilian Communist Party and other heads of state, governments, political parties, organizations and high-ranking officials sent floral baskets to DPRK missions on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il. He was presented with gifts by the China Association for International Friendly Contact, the Beijing Association for International Friendly Contact, the Dandong Municipal People's Government of Liaoning Province in China, the general chairperson of the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle, the vice-chairman of the National Democratic Party of Egypt, the director of the State Academic Moiseyev Dance Company of Russia, the honorary manager of Voluntad Publishing House of Ecuador, the editor of the Bangladesh newspaper Blits and the chairman of the Egyptian Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meetings, seminars, lectures, book and photo exhibitions and film shows and other celebrations were held in more than 70 countries including Laos, Mongolia, Iran, Pakistan, Sweden, the Czech Republic, Austria, France, Guinea, Uganda, Democratic Congo, Tanzania, Peru, Ecuador, Mexico, Brazil and Australia.
 The participants in celebrations expressed boundless respect and reverence for Kim Jong Il, a great teacher of progressive humankind and an outstanding leader for accomplishing the cause of global independence.

